@Node INEA2 "Invasion -- Earth > The Fourth Dimension [#2]"

 @{b}The Fourth Dimension [#2]@{ub} (1998)
 
 The alien attack is repelled, although not without fatalities. A homing device
 has been found embedded in Terrell's tooth. Tucker removes it and as they take
 it for analysis, Tucker and four military personnel are abducted, including
 the RAF doctor, Wing Commander Friday. Drake supervises Terrell's transfer to
 a high security RAF base. On the way, an unidentified contact heading for the
 convoy causes Reece to order that Drake kill the prisoner. His hesitation
 proves fortuitous when the contact is revealed as unthreatening, but tension
 is high. In the alien craft Tucker and the abductees undergo a series of
 painful and frightening invasive tests. Although understandably distraught,
 Tucker remains alert enough to register the organic construction of the ship.
 
 On Earth, the interrogation of Terrell proves fruitless. When a signal is
 picked up on radar, Flight Lieutenant Radcliffe leads his retrieval team to
 its location, accompanied by Drake. After a terrifying close encounter, they
 discover that Friday and two of the airmen have been returned. Drake is
 distressed to see no sign of Tucker, who remains captive on board the alien
 ship. From her observations she has realised that these beings have the
 ability to exploit higher spatial dimensions. Her attempt to explain her
 theory to the remaining airman fails, and he dies shortly afterwards. Alone
 and terrified she scratches an ideogram into the flesh of her own forearm so
 that she can get a message out even if they kill her. It reads n-D, indicating
 that they are confronting an enemy with multi-dimensional capabilities. We
 will know them as the nDs.
 
 Against orders, Drake decides to interrogate Terrell himself. He bonds with
 him and before he leaves, Terrell reveals his army number. Radcliffe runs a
 check and they discover that Terrell disappeared in 1944. When Reece orders
 that Tucker be kept under surveillance, Drake volunteers for the job. Together
 they start analysing Terrell's escape pod. Tucker is putting a business-like
 face on it, but Drake senses her distance. He tries to ask Emily about her
 mother, and when Tucker discovers him talking to her she reacts aggressively.
 
 Friday and the other airmen are 'activated' by the nDs. One is restrained, and
 the other killed. Having been allowed home under guard, Friday escapes with
 ease and begins a journey to an unknown destination. Drake demands that Tucker
 tell him what happened to her. She confides in him, but begs that she's not
 made unfit for duty - she has to keep working on discovering the nDs
 objective. He agrees. Looking again at the results of medical tests performed
 on the abductees, Drake discovers evidence of implants. He is relieved to find
 that Tucker appears to be clear. Alone, Tucker regards the scratch on her arm
 with dread. It isn't healing normally at all.
 
