@Node INEA4 "Invasion -- Earth > The Fall Of Man [#4]"

 @{b}The Fall Of Man [#4]@{ub} (1998)
 
 Reece and Air Marshal Peter Bentley observe a specialist team of pathologists
 as they perform an autopsy on the dead Echo. Afterwards, Bentley interviews
 Terrell and is not convinced by his story. He makes a final demand for proof
 from Reece. Meanwhile, Preston is increasingly concerned about the changes
 occurring in Tucker. She appears to be undergoing a similar process to the
 Echoes. Although she does not tell Tucker of her conclusions, Preston is
 hopeful of being able to test an anti-nD toxin on her.
 
 Reece decides that there is only one way to get the proof they need: to
 capture an nD. Apart from Drake, his officers are unconvinced. Knox in
 particular is concerned that without fully understanding the nature of the
 enemy the plan is needlessly risky.
 
 Tucker is not convinced by Preston's attempts at reassurance and reluctantly
 decides to send Emily away to safety. Although aware it is best for her
 daughter, Tucker is distraught.
 
 Preston takes her findings to Knox, concerned that Tucker poses a threat to
 security. The medics remove the stigma from Tucker's arm. As she recovers
 relieved that the nD flesh has been taken away, Knox and Preston ask her to
 remove herself from duty. She refuses to stop her work.
 
 Radcliffe has alerted local police stations to be on the lookout for Friday,
 telling them simply that he is AWOL. Friday reaches Kirkhaven just as local
 policewoman, DS Rebecca Holland is alerted. Friday cuts open his arms and
 plunges into the reservoir, bleeding to death in the water, infecting the
 supply to the town.
 
 Plans to capture an nD are put into action. Terrell has refused to be of any
 assistance, thinking the plan insane but an impassioned plea from Tucker
 brings him round.
 
 In Kirkhaven, people start to fall ill with bizarre symptoms. Local GP, Dr.
 John Vickers examines Jenny Marchant, one of the townspeople with the disease,
 and is baffled.
 
 Preparations for the capture attempt are finalised. Nick is dismayed when he
 realises that it isn't a peaceful attempt to communicate. Reece gives the
 order to transmit the signal that is part of the trap. When the nD finally
 comes it causes havoc and there are fatalities. Just as they gather themselves
 after the attack the nDs return, ignoring the chance to harm Tucker and taking
 Terrell. He screams that they can't take him alive. Drake kills him with a
 single shot to the head. It is a devastating blow.
 
 The next morning, Tucker is dismayed to find the nD tissue regrowing on her
 arm. After what happened the night before, she is devastated to think that the
 nDs still have some purpose for her. Drake stands by her.
 
 In Kirkhaven, Vickers has alerted the Department of Public Health about the
 unexplained epidemic. Friday's body is found and Holland calls Vickers in.
 
 Preston cannot offer any reassurance this time and Tucker realises the truth
 about what is happening to her. She is anguished and angry and rejects Drake,
 telling him that everything that has happened is his fault. He is devastated.
 
